4:41:40 AM [express] POST /api/mealplan 200 in 60650ms :: {"week_summary":"20-year-old moderately active male (170 cm, 65 kg, Vata-dominant) aiming to boost immunity with Indian cuisine, no allergies or health conditions, moderate budget, and up to 1 hour for cooking.","hydration":"Aim for ~2.3–2.5 liters of fluids daily, favoring warm water or herbal teas; keep a 1-liter bottle at your desk and finish it by lunch, then refill and finish the second by early evening to support Vata balance and immunity.","weekly_strategy":"This week focuses on warm, lightly spiced, ghee-enriched Indian meals to ground Vata and strengthen immunity with ample seasonal vegetables, fruits rich in vitamin C, and high-quality proteins. Each day combines rice, millets, lentils, and dairy with priority Ayurvedic foods like amla, tulsi, ginger, turmeric, and garlic. Snacks are kept simple, warm, and digestion-friendly to maintain stable energy and support Ojas (vital immunity).","clinician_note":"","days":[{"day":1,"day_name":"Monday","meals":{"breakfast":{"dish_name":"Vegetable Moong Dal Cheela with Mint-Coriander Chutney","ingredients":["yellow moong dal (soaked and ground)","finely grated carrot","finely chopped methi leaves","finely chopped coriander leaves","grated ginger","cumin seeds","turmeric powder","black pepper","salt","ghee for cooking","mint leaves","coriander leaves","lemon juice","green chili (optional, mild)","roasted peanuts (small amount) for chutney"],"portion":"3 cheelas (~250g batter total) + 2 tbsp chutney","macros":{"protein":"20g","carbs":"55g","fat":"14g","calories":"470 kcal"},"why":"Warm, soft cheelas with ghee and spices like ginger, cumin, and turmeric balance Vata and support digestion and immunity, while moong dal gives light but high-quality protein.","substitutions":["Replace moong dal with urad dal for a slightly richer version","Use coconut chutney instead of mint-coriander chutney if you prefer milder flavors"]},"morning_snack":{"dish_name":"Papaya-Amla Fruit Bowl with Soaked Almonds","ingredients":["ripe papaya cubes","fresh amla grated or finely chopped (or amla juice)","1 tsp honey","soaked and peeled almonds","pinch of black pepper"],"portion":"1 small bowl papaya (~150g) + 1 small amla + 6 almonds","macros":{"protein":"5g","carbs":"30g","fat":"7g","calories":"220 kcal"},"why":"Papaya and amla provide vitamin C and antioxidants to enhance immunity, while soaked almonds nourish Vata and add healthy fats.","substitutions":["Swap papaya with orange segments if papaya not available","Use walnut halves instead of almonds"]},"lunch":{"dish_name":"Jeera Rice with Mixed Vegetable Moong Dal Tadka and Beet-Carrot Sambharo","ingredients":["white rice","ghee","cumin seeds","salt","yellow moong dal","onion","tomato","garlic","ginger","turmeric powder","coriander powder","curry leaves","mustard seeds","green peas","diced carrot","diced pumpkin","diced bottle gourd","fresh coriander leaves","grated beetroot","grated carrot","lemon juice","roasted sesame seeds (small amount)","pinch of black pepper"],"portion":"1.5 cups cooked jeera rice (~250g) + 1.5 cups dal (~250g) + 1/2 cup beet-carrot sambharo","macros":{"protein":"24g","carbs":"90g","fat":"18g","calories":"700 kcal"},"why":"Jeera rice and moong dal provide a comforting, easily digestible Vata-balancing combo, while beetroot, carrot, and pumpkin add antioxidants and carotenoids to support immune health.","substitutions":["Replace moong dal with masoor dal if you want a slightly stronger flavor","Use brown rice instead of white rice for extra fiber if digestion is strong"]},"evening_snack":{"dish_name":"Tulsi-Ginger Herbal Tea with Roasted Chana","ingredients":["water","fresh tulsi leaves","sliced fresh ginger","cardamom pod","1 tsp jaggery (optional)","roasted chana (whole black gram, skinless)","pinch of black salt"],"portion":"1 cup tea (~200 ml) + 1 small katori roasted chana (~25g)","macros":{"protein":"5g","carbs":"16g","fat":"1g","calories":"95 kcal"},"why":"Warm tulsi-ginger tea is ideal for boosting respiratory immunity and calming Vata, while roasted chana offers light protein and keeps blood sugar steady.","substitutions":["Replace roasted chana with a small handful of roasted peanuts","Use lemongrass instead of tulsi if tulsi leaves not available"]},"dinner":{"dish_name":"Soft Phulka Roti with Methi Aloo Sabzi and Lauki (Bottle Gourd) Yogurt Curry","ingredients":["whole wheat flour","water","ghee for brushing","potatoes","fresh methi leaves","onion","turmeric powder","cumin seeds","coriander powder","ginger-garlic paste","salt","bottle gourd cubes","fresh curd (slightly warm, not chilled)","curry leaves","mustard seeds","green chili (very little)","fresh coriander leaves"],"portion":"3 small phulkas (~90g flour) + 1 cup methi aloo (~180g) + 3/4 cup lauki yogurt curry (~150g)","macros":{"protein":"16g","carbs":"82g","fat":"17g","calories":"620 kcal"},"why":"Warm phulkas with ghee and mildly spiced methi aloo ground Vata, while bottle gourd with warm curd soothes the gut and supports immunity through probiotics.","substitutions":["Swap potato with sweet potato for a more Vata-pacifying option","Replace lauki with pumpkin if bottle gourd is unavailable"]}}},{"day":2,"day_name":"Tuesday","meals":{"breakfast":{"dish_name":"Masala Vegetable Upma with Curry Leaves","ingredients":["semolina (rava)","ghee","mustard seeds","cumin seeds","curry leaves","chopped onion","chopped carrot","green peas","chopped tomato","grated ginger","turmeric powder","salt","fresh coriander leaves","lemon wedge"],"portion":"1 medium bowl upma (~300g)","macros":{"protein":"10g","carbs":"60g","fat":"14g","calories":"460 kcal"},"why":"Warm, soft, ghee-roasted upma with vegetables and curry leaves is grounding for Vata and provides steady energy plus antioxidants from carrots, peas, and tomatoes.","substitutions":["Replace semolina with broken wheat (dalia) for a higher fiber option","Use a small amount of cashews instead of peas if you prefer fewer legumes in the morning"]},"morning_snack":{"dish_name":"Guava Slices with Black Salt and Chili Powder","ingredients":["ripe but firm guava","black salt","very mild red chili powder","few drops lemon juice"],"portion":"1 medium guava (~150g) sliced","macros":{"protein":"3g","carbs":"22g","fat":"1g","calories":"110 kcal"},"why":"Guava is rich in vitamin C and fiber for immunity and gut health, while a pinch of black salt and mild chili aids digestion without aggravating Vata when taken in moderation.","substitutions":["Replace guava with orange or sweet lime segments","Skip chili powder entirely if you are heat-sensitive"]},"lunch":{"dish_name":"Rajma Curry with Steamed Rice and Simple Cucumber-Carrot Kachumber","ingredients":["kidney beans (rajma) soaked and boiled","onion","tomato","ginger-garlic paste","turmeric powder","coriander powder","cumin seeds","garam masala (very small amount)","ghee or oil","salt","fresh coriander leaves","white rice","cucumber","carrot","lemon juice","black pepper","pinch of roasted cumin powder"],"portion":"1.5 cups cooked rice (~250g) + 1.25 cups rajma (~220g) + 1/2 cup kachumber","macros":{"protein":"25g","carbs":"95g","fat":"16g","calories":"720 kcal"},"why":"Rajma with rice offers complete vegetarian protein and stable energy, while warming spices, ghee, and cooked beans (well-soaked) make it more Vata-friendly and immunity-supportive.","substitutions":["Replace rajma with chole (chickpeas) if preferred","Use brown rice instead of white if your digestion handles more fiber"]},"evening_snack":{"dish_name":"Warm Haldi Doodh (Turmeric Milk) with a Small Date","ingredients":["cow's milk or toned milk","turmeric powder","freshly ground black pepper","cardamom powder","small piece of jaggery or 1/2 tsp honey (added after slightly cooling if using honey)","1 soft date"],"portion":"1 cup milk (~200 ml) + 1 date (~10g)","macros":{"protein":"7g","carbs":"18g","fat":"7g","calories":"170 kcal"},"why":"Warm turmeric milk with black pepper enhances absorption of curcumin for immune support and nourishes Vata, while a date adds a quick natural energy boost.","substitutions":["Use almond milk if avoiding dairy","Replace date with 2 dried figs if you want more fiber"]},"dinner":{"dish_name":"Soft Khichdi with Pumpkin, Carrot and a Side of Lightly Spiced Okra Stir-Fry","ingredients":["white rice","yellow moong dal","ghee","cumin seeds","turmeric powder","salt","diced pumpkin","diced carrot","fresh ginger","water","okra (bhindi)","onion","coriander powder","amchur (very little, optional)","mustard seeds","fresh coriander leaves"],"portion":"1.5 bowls khichdi (~300g) + 1 cup okra stir-fry (~150g)","macros":{"protein":"18g","carbs":"78g","fat":"16g","calories":"600 kcal"},"why":"Soft khichdi is ideal for Vata, improving digestion and recovery, while pumpkin and carrot add beta carotene for immunity and okra gives fiber and gentle bulk.","substitutions":["Replace pumpkin with sweet potato cubes in khichdi","Swap okra with a simple stir-fry of beans and carrots"]}}},{"day":3,"day_name":"Wednesday","meals":{"breakfast":{"dish_name":"Sweet Potato Poha with Peas and Peanuts","ingredients":["thick poha (flattened rice)","boiled and diced sweet potato","green peas","onion","curry leaves","mustard seeds","turmeric powder","green chili (minimal)","peanuts","ghee or oil","salt","lemon juice","fresh coriander leaves"],"portion":"1 medium bowl poha (~280g)","macros":{"protein":"9g","carbs":"62g","fat":"14g","calories":"460 kcal"},"why":"Sweet potato and poha make a warm, grounding breakfast for Vata, while peas and peanuts add protein and healthy fats to sustain immunity and energy.","substitutions":["Replace peanuts with cashews for a milder taste","Skip chili and add extra ginger if you’re sensitive to spice"]},"morning_snack":{"dish_name":"Apple Slices with Cinnamon and Walnut Crumble","ingredients":["medium apple","crushed walnuts","cinnamon powder","1 tsp honey (optional)"],"portion":"1 apple (~140g) + 6 walnut halves (~15g)","macros":{"protein":"3g","carbs":"27g","fat":"9g","calories":"210 kcal"},"why":"Apple offers fiber for gut health, walnuts add omega-3s supportive of immune function, and warming cinnamon helps balance Vata.","substitutions":["Replace walnuts with almonds if preferred","Use pear instead of apple in cooler seasons"]},"lunch":{"dish_name":"Quinoa Pulav with Drumsticks, Carrot, Peas and Raita","ingredients":["quinoa","ghee or oil","cumin seeds","cloves","bay leaf","onion","tomato","drumstick pieces (moringa pods)","carrot cubes","green peas","turmeric powder","garam masala (small)","salt","fresh coriander leaves","curd","finely chopped cucumber","roasted cumin powder","black salt"],"portion":"1.5 cups cooked quinoa pulav (~250g) + 3/4 cup raita (~150g)","macros":{"protein":"20g","carbs":"70g","fat":"16g","calories":"620 kcal"},"why":"Quinoa provides complete protein and minerals, while drumsticks and peas enhance iron and vitamin C content, all cooked warmly with ghee and spices to support Vata and immunity.","substitutions":["Replace quinoa with little millet or foxtail millet","Use bottle gourd cubes instead of drumsticks if not available"]},"evening_snack":{"dish_name":"Light Vegetable Soup with Garlic and Black Pepper","ingredients":["carrot","bottle gourd","tomato","onion","garlic","ginger","black pepper","salt","ghee or oil","water","fresh coriander leaves"],"portion":"1 medium bowl soup (~220 ml)","macros":{"protein":"3g","carbs":"12g","fat":"4g","calories":"90 kcal"},"why":"Warm, light vegetable soup with garlic, ginger, and black pepper is excellent for Vata digestion and respiratory immunity, especially towards evening.","substitutions":["Add a few pieces of beetroot instead of tomato if you want it less acidic","Use olive oil instead of ghee if desired"]},"dinner":{"dish_name":"Barley Khichda with Mixed Lentils and Caramelized Onions","ingredients":["pearled barley","split green moong dal","masoor dal","ghee","cumin seeds","bay leaf","clove","onion (one for tempering, one for caramelizing)","turmeric powder","ginger-garlic paste","salt","fresh coriander leaves","lemon wedge"],"portion":"1.5 bowls khichda (~300g)","macros":{"protein":"22g","carbs":"78g","fat":"14g","calories":"620 kcal"},"why":"Barley with mixed lentils offers slow-release carbs and protein, while ghee and gently spiced tempering make it grounding and suitable for Vata and immune nourishment.","substitutions":["Replace barley with rice if you want something lighter","Use only moong dal instead of mixed lentils for easier digestion"]}}},{"day":4,"day_name":"Thursday","meals":{"breakfast":{"dish_name":"Masala Oats Porridge with Vegetables","ingredients":["rolled oats","ghee or oil","cumin seeds","mustard seeds","onion","tomato","carrot cubes","green peas","turmeric powder","black pepper","salt","water or thin buttermilk","fresh coriander leaves"],"portion":"1 bowl savory oats (~300g)","macros":{"protein":"11g","carbs":"55g","fat":"12g","calories":"430 kcal"},"why":"Warm, soft oats with spices and vegetables calm Vata and offer beta-glucan fiber for immunity and heart health.","substitutions":["Use broken wheat (dalia) instead of oats","Swap peas for finely chopped spinach"]},"morning_snack":{"dish_name":"Pomegranate and Orange Bowl","ingredients":["pomegranate arils","orange segments","few mint leaves","pinch of black pepper"],"portion":"1 small bowl (~180g total fruit)","macros":{"protein":"3g","carbs":"35g","fat":"1g","calories":"150 kcal"},"why":"Pomegranate and orange provide vitamin C and antioxidants that build immunity while remaining light and suitable as a mid-morning snack for Vata.","substitutions":["Replace orange with sweet lime","Add a few pieces of apple if you need more volume"]},"lunch":{"dish_name":"Curd Rice with Tempered Curry Leaves and Side of Beetroot Poriyal","ingredients":["cooked white rice","fresh curd (room temperature)","milk (optional to adjust consistency)","salt","ghee or oil","mustard seeds","cumin seeds","curry leaves","grated ginger (very little)","chopped coriander leaves","grated beetroot","grated coconut (optional, small)","green chili (minimal)","lemon juice"],"portion":"1.5 cups curd rice (~280g) + 3/4 cup beetroot poriyal (~150g)","macros":{"protein":"15g","carbs":"75g","fat":"16g","calories":"560 kcal"},"why":"Curd rice at room temperature with curry leaves soothes the gut and supports beneficial bacteria, while beetroot adds folate and antioxidants important for immunity and blood health.","substitutions":["Use brown rice if digestion is strong","Swap beetroot with carrot poriyal if preferred"]},"evening_snack":{"dish_name":"Spiced Buttermilk (Chaas) with Roasted Makhana","ingredients":["thin buttermilk (curd + water)","roasted cumin powder","black salt","chopped coriander leaves","crushed ginger (very small)","makhana (fox nuts)","ghee","pinch of turmeric","pinch of black pepper"],"portion":"1 glass chaas (~200 ml) + 1 small bowl roasted makhana (~15g)","macros":{"protein":"6g","carbs":"14g","fat":"5g","calories":"140 kcal"},"why":"Spiced buttermilk aids digestion and balances Vata-Pitta, while roasted makhana offers light protein and minerals without heaviness.","substitutions":["Replace makhana with a handful of puffed rice chivda (lightly spiced)","Skip ginger in chaas if you feel too warm"]},"dinner":{"dish_name":"Mixed Vegetable Sambar with Steamed Idlis","ingredients":["idli rice","urad dal","fenugreek seeds","water","salt","toor dal","drumsticks","bottle gourd","carrot","tomato","onion","tamarind pulp (small amount)","sambar powder (mild)","turmeric powder","mustard seeds","curry leaves","dry red chili (optional, small)","ghee or sesame oil","fresh coriander leaves"],"portion":"4 medium idlis (~240g) + 1.5 cups vegetable sambar (~250g)","macros":{"protein":"20g","carbs":"86g","fat":"12g","calories":"610 kcal"},"why":"Soft idlis are easy to digest for Vata, and sambar with drumsticks, bottle gourd, and carrots delivers protein, fiber, and immune-supportive antioxidants in a warm, soupy form.","substitutions":["Replace idlis with dosa if you prefer a crisp option (add a little more ghee)","Use moong dal instead of toor dal for lighter digestion"]}}},{"day":5,"day_name":"Friday","meals":{"breakfast":{"dish_name":"Besan Chilla Stuffed with Paneer and Spinach","ingredients":["besan (gram flour)","water","turmeric powder","ajwain (carom seeds)","salt","ghee or oil for cooking","grated paneer","finely chopped spinach","onion (finely chopped)","black pepper","fresh coriander leaves"],"portion":"2 large stuffed chillas (~260g total)","macros":{"protein":"22g","carbs":"38g","fat":"18g","calories":"480 kcal"},"why":"High-protein besan and paneer with warm spices and ghee support muscle recovery and immunity, while the soft, warm texture is Vata-friendly.","substitutions":["Replace paneer with boiled mashed peas and potatoes","Use finely chopped methi leaves instead of spinach for a stronger Ayurvedic touch"]},"morning_snack":{"dish_name":"Fresh Coconut and Banana Slices with Cardamom","ingredients":["ripe banana","fresh coconut slices or grated coconut","cardamom powder"],"portion":"1 small banana (~80g) + 2 tbsp grated coconut (~20g)","macros":{"protein":"2g","carbs":"25g","fat":"7g","calories":"170 kcal"},"why":"Banana and coconut are grounding, nourishing foods that pacify Vata and provide quick energy and healthy fats to support overall vitality.","substitutions":["Use mango slices in season instead of banana","Replace coconut with a few soaked almonds if fresh coconut not available"]},"lunch":{"dish_name":"Mixed Vegetable Curry with Jowar Roti","ingredients":["jowar flour","warm water","salt","ghee for brushing","onion","tomato","garlic","ginger","cauliflower florets","carrot","peas","potato cubes","turmeric powder","coriander powder","cumin seeds","garam masala (small)","oil or ghee","fresh coriander leaves"],"portion":"3 small jowar rotis (~90g flour) + 1.5 cups vegetable curry (~250g)","macros":{"protein":"14g","carbs":"82g","fat":"15g","calories":"600 kcal"},"why":"Gluten-free jowar rotis with ghee and a mixed vegetable curry provide complex carbs, fiber, and micronutrients, all cooked in a warming style that suits Vata and immune health.","substitutions":["Replace jowar roti with whole wheat phulka if jowar is hard to roll","Swap potatoes with pumpkin or sweet potato"]},"evening_snack":{"dish_name":"Lemon-Coriander Rasam (Light South Indian Broth)","ingredients":["water","tomato","crushed garlic","cumin seeds","black pepper","mustard seeds","curry leaves","ghee","fresh coriander leaves","lemon juice","salt"],"portion":"1 bowl rasam (~220 ml)","macros":{"protein":"2g","carbs":"8g","fat":"3g","calories":"60 kcal"},"why":"Light, tangy, warm rasam with garlic, pepper, and coriander is excellent for immunity and digestion, especially balancing for a Vata constitution in the evening.","substitutions":["Add a spoon of cooked toor dal for more body and protein","Use ginger instead of garlic if you prefer milder flavor"]},"dinner":{"dish_name":"Paneer Bhurji with Peas and Jeera Brown Rice","ingredients":["paneer, crumbled","onion","tomato","green peas","ginger-garlic paste","turmeric powder","coriander powder","cumin seeds","garam masala (small)","ghee or oil","salt","fresh coriander leaves","brown rice","ghee","cumin seeds"],"portion":"1 cup paneer bhurji (~180g) + 1 cup cooked jeera brown rice (~200g)","macros":{"protein":"24g","carbs":"72g","fat":"22g","calories":"680 kcal"},"why":"Paneer and peas give strong vegetarian protein to support immune cells and muscle, while jeera brown rice offers complex carbs and warm digestion-supportive cumin for Vata.","substitutions":["Replace paneer with tofu if avoiding dairy","Use white rice instead of brown if you prefer softer texture at night"]}}},{"day":6,"day_name":"Saturday","meals":{"breakfast":{"dish_name":"Idiyappam (String Hoppers) with Vegetable Coconut Stew","ingredients":["rice flour","hot water","salt","oil for greasing","thin coconut milk","onion","carrot","potato","peas","ginger","green chili (minimal)","curry leaves","cloves","cinnamon stick","black peppercorns","salt"],"portion":"4 small idiyappams (~200g) + 1 cup veg stew (~200g)","macros":{"protein":"9g","carbs":"70g","fat":"14g","calories":"520 kcal"},"why":"Soft rice idiyappam with warm coconut vegetable stew is gentle on Vata digestion and the coconut adds healthy fats that nourish tissues and support immunity.","substitutions":["Replace idiyappam with plain steamed rice","Use cow’s milk plus a little coconut instead of full coconut milk for lighter stew"]},"morning_snack":{"dish_name":"Mango-Amla Smoothie (No Ice)","ingredients":["ripe mango pieces","fresh amla or amla powder","room temperature milk or water","cardamom powder","1 tsp honey (optional)"],"portion":"1 glass smoothie (~200 ml)","macros":{"protein":"5g","carbs":"32g","fat":"3g","calories":"180 kcal"},"why":"Mango and amla provide a strong hit of vitamin C, carotenoids, and antioxidants that bolster immunity, blended without ice to keep it warm enough for Vata.","substitutions":["Replace mango with papaya in off-season","Use coconut water instead of milk for a dairy-free version"]},"lunch":{"dish_name":"Drumstick Sambar with Red Rice and Simple Cabbage Thoran","ingredients":["red rice","toor dal","drumsticks (moringa)","tomato","onion","turmeric powder","sambar powder (mild)","tamarind (small amount)","mustard seeds","curry leaves","dry red chili (optional)","ghee or oil","fresh coriander leaves","cabbage, finely shredded","grated coconut","green chili (minimal)","cumin seeds","salt"],"portion":"1.5 cups cooked red rice (~250g) + 1.5 cups drumstick sambar (~250g) + 1/2 cup cabbage thoran (~80g)","macros":{"protein":"22g","carbs":"92g","fat":"14g","calories":"650 kcal"},"why":"Red rice and dal give complex carbs and protein, while drumsticks (moringa) are highly valued in Ayurveda for their nutrient density and immunity support.","substitutions":["Use white rice if red rice feels too heavy","Replace cabbage with beans poriyal if you prefer"]},"evening_snack":{"dish_name":"Ginger-Lemon-Honey Warm Water and Handful of Chivda","ingredients":["warm water","fresh lemon juice","grated ginger","1 tsp honey (added after slight cooling)","homemade or store-bought poha chivda (lightly roasted, minimal oil, peanuts, curry leaves, mustard seeds, turmeric)"],"portion":"1 glass (~200 ml) ginger-lemon-honey water + 1 small handful chivda (~20g)","macros":{"protein":"3g","carbs":"18g","fat":"4g","calories":"120 kcal"},"why":"Ginger-lemon-honey water supports digestion, throat health, and immunity, while light chivda satisfies evening hunger without burdening Vata.","substitutions":["Skip honey if you have it frequently and just use lemon-ginger water","Replace chivda with a few soaked almonds and raisins"]},"dinner":{"dish_name":"Soft Vegetable Dalia (Broken Wheat) Khichdi with Ghee Tadka","ingredients":["broken wheat (dalia)","yellow moong dal","bottle gourd cubes","carrot cubes","peas","turmeric powder","salt","water","ghee","cumin seeds","grated ginger","fresh coriander leaves"],"portion":"1.5 bowls dalia khichdi (~300g)","macros":{"protein":"16g","carbs":"78g","fat":"12g","calories":"570 kcal"},"why":"Soft, one-pot dalia khichdi with vegetables and ghee is very grounding for Vata at night and provides balanced carbs, protein, and micronutrients for immune restoration.","substitutions":["Replace broken wheat with rice if you avoid wheat","Swap bottle gourd for pumpkin"]}}},{"day":7,"day_name":"Sunday","meals":{"breakfast":{"dish_name":"Stuffed Paratha with Aloo-Peas and Side of Homemade Curd","ingredients":["whole wheat flour","water","salt","boiled potatoes","boiled green peas","coriander leaves","grated ginger","cumin powder","amchur powder (small)","ghee for cooking","fresh curd (room temperature)"],"portion":"2 medium stuffed parathas (~200g) + 1/2 cup curd (~100g)","macros":{"protein":"14g","carbs":"70g","fat":"18g","calories":"560 kcal"},"why":"Warm ghee-cooked stuffed parathas are grounding and satisfying for Vata on a relaxed day, and peas plus curd add protein and probiotics for immune support.","substitutions":["Use sweet potato instead of regular potato in the stuffing","Swap curd with a small bowl of lassi if you prefer to drink it"]},"morning_snack":{"dish_name":"Mixed Fruit Plate with Pineapple, Papaya and Apple","ingredients":["pineapple slices","papaya cubes","apple slices","pinch of black pepper","few mint leaves"],"portion":"1 plate (~200g mixed fruit)","macros":{"protein":"3g","carbs":"40g","fat":"1g","calories":"170 kcal"},"why":"A mix of pineapple, papaya, and apple provides enzymes and vitamin C that support digestion and immunity without being too heavy for Vata.","substitutions":["Replace pineapple with orange if acidity bothers you","Swap apple with guava for extra vitamin C"]},"lunch":{"dish_name":"Chole (Chickpea Curry) with Jeera Rice and Kachumber Salad","ingredients":["chickpeas soaked and boiled","onion","tomato","ginger-garlic paste","turmeric powder","coriander powder","cumin seeds","chole masala (small)","ghee or oil","salt","fresh coriander leaves","white rice","ghee","cumin seeds","cucumber","tomato","onion","lemon juice","black pepper","salt"],"portion":"1.25 cups chole (~220g) + 1.5 cups jeera rice (~250g) + 1/2 cup kachumber","macros":{"protein":"24g","carbs":"96g","fat":"18g","calories":"720 kcal"},"why":"Chole with jeera rice delivers robust plant protein and iron to support immune cells, with cumin and ghee improving digestibility for Vata when beans are well-cooked.","substitutions":["Replace chickpeas with whole masoor or rajma if preferred","Use brown rice instead of white for more fiber"]},"evening_snack":{"dish_name":"Cardamom-Saffron Warm Milk with A Few Almonds","ingredients":["milk","cardamom powder","few strands saffron","small piece jaggery or 1/2 tsp honey (added after cooling slightly if using honey)","soaked and peeled almonds"],"portion":"1 cup milk (~200 ml) + 5 almonds (~7g)","macros":{"protein":"8g","carbs":"17g","fat":"8g","calories":"190 kcal"},"why":"Warm spiced milk with saffron and almonds nourishes Ojas (vital energy) and calms Vata, supporting restful recovery and immune strength.","substitutions":["Use almond milk or oat milk if avoiding dairy","Replace almonds with 2 walnut halves"]},"dinner":{"dish_name":"Tomato-Carrot Shorba with Vegetable Pulao","ingredients":["basmati rice","mixed vegetables (carrot, peas, beans, small potato cubes)","onion","whole spices (cumin seeds, bay leaf, cloves, cinnamon)","ghee or oil","turmeric powder","salt","fresh coriander leaves","tomatoes","carrots","garlic","ginger","black pepper","cumin powder","ghee","water"],"portion":"1.25 cups veg pulao (~230g) + 1 bowl shorba (~200 ml)","macros":{"protein":"12g","carbs":"72g","fat":"14g","calories":"520 kcal"},"why":"Lightly spiced veg pulao paired with warm tomato-carrot shorba is easy to digest at night and provides antioxidants like lycopene and beta carotene for immune support.","substitutions":["Replace basmati rice with quinoa for more protein","Add a spoon of boiled moong dal into the shorba for extra protein"]}}}]}
